news.title: Kamdhenu to list paints business post de-merger: Satish Agarwal, CMD
news.para: ​Kamdhenu is in the process of separating its steel and paints business with an aim to increase its reach and customer base in the market.

news.title: Macrotech Developers looking to enter Bengaluru
news.para: Abhishek Lodha said the company would deploy Rs 3,000 crore, out of the total Rs 4,000 crore recently being raised via sale of shares to institutional investors, for growth in the capital-light manner in Mumbai Metropolitan Region (MMR) and Pune.

news.title: Delhi government gives Rs 5,000 each to 2.95 lakh construction workers
news.para: ​Delhi has 6 lakh registered construction workers and another one lakh are in the process of getting registered. The amount will be credited to the accounts of the remaining workers in the next two days, the statement said.

news.title: Robust regulatory mechanism under RERA: Centre on uniform builder-buyer agreement
news.para: On November 8, the Supreme Court said a model builder-buyer agreement is an important matter in public interest, which is required in the real estate sector, and sought Centre's reply in the matter.

news.title: Income tax searches carried out on two Ludhiana-based developers
news.para: "The major finding emanating from these search and seizure operations of both the groups is about the receipt of unaccounted cash by these groups by way of on-money on property transactions," the Ministry of Finance said.

news.title: Uphaar cinema fire: Court reserves order on suspending Ansals' jail terms
news.para: Additional Sessions Judge Anil Antil reserved the order on appeals filed by the Ansals against their conviction and jail terms by a magisterial court.

news.title: Locals stop construction of Dalmia cement plant, demand jobs
news.para: The land on which the protest took place actually belongs to Jharkhand Industrial Area Development Authourity (JIADA). It was acquired in 1962-63 by JIADA after making payments to the land owners.

news.title: Georgia outlines plans to improve slow pace of rental help
news.para: The improvement plans were submitted last week to the U.S. Department of the Treasury. If they are not approved, the state risks losing some of the $550 million it was allocated in a first round of federal rental aid.

news.title: Hong Kong firms scoop up properties from Chinese developers in distress
news.para: Developers including China Evergrande Group and Kaisa Group Holdings Ltd, struggling under billions of dollars in debt, have sold some assets in recent months to Hong Kong developers to help ease liquidity stress back home.

news.title: Chennai: Chengalpet residents flag civic woes
news.para: Protection of Palar river, conservation of water bodies and high property taxes were issues raised by residents of Chengalpet as a public hearing on bringing the entire district under the Chennai Metropolitan Area (CMA).

news.title: East Delhi civic body proposes increase in property tax, new levies
news.para: EDMC commissioner Vikas Anand proposed to increase property tax on residential properties in C, D and E categories from 11% to 13 %, and in F, G and H categories from 7% to 10%.

news.title: ICRA revises Home First Finance's long term credit ratings
news.para: The credit rating agency revised the outlook for Home First Finance 's Rs 3,500 crore- term loan and Rs 400 crore- non- convertible debentures (NCDs) programme from stable to positive.

news.title: Bureau of Energy Efficiency awards E3 certification to Jindal Bricks
news.para: The E3 scheme is a voluntary certification offered by the BEE to accelerate the technology shift in the building industry and promote the adoption of energy-efficient building materials and sustainable building materials.

news.title: Jewar airport's builder to pay Rs 10 lakh per day for delay
news.para: Zurich AG, and the UP government had signed the final agreement, it had been decided the company would be liable to pay 0.1% of the bank guarantee it had deposited every day as liquidated damages if the project breached the deadline.

news.title: Civic amenities neglected as takeover pending: Mayfield Garden residents
news.para: Spread across 327 acres in sectors 47, 50, 51, 52 and 57, the township was developed two decades ago. Residents said they were relieved when the government announced the transfer of the colony to MCG in 2019.
